{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013CUV8X5hnetTwojbx9k6oT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue with my scripts is they use subprocess to call python3.14 from within python3.14, which adds overhead and might be causing issues. Let me redesign — write scripts that run directly with python3.14, calling Spot APIs directly without nested subprocesses.\n\nLet me also rethink my strategy. Instead of trying to solve the hardest instances, I should:\n\n1. **Re-optimize existing solutions** — many have ref_size=0 but we produce huge circuits. Use Spot's simplification more aggressively.\n2. **Attack tractable unsolved families** — use ltlsynt directly (it's a command-line tool, doesn't need python) for families that might respond to different algorithms\n\n\n3. **Try ltlsynt directly** for unsolved instances — it can be faster than spot game for some cases\n\nSo I'll create three focused scripts: one to re-optimize the best candidates using Spot's mealy simplification, another to run ltlsynt with decomposition on unsolved instances, and a third to target specific families. The core problem is the subprocess overhead from nested python calls, so I'm eliminating that entirely by running everything directly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":502,"cache_read_input_tokens":69242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":502},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6882dd44-b12a-40ea-abce-8556d98170ba","uuid":"dc19c1d0-d5f7-4190-bc9d-2f345715d733"}
