{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q4pehXjDLs2GYXE6PS1CB1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are 87 remaining in tractable families, but they have larger signals (10-500+) so they'll take longer. The biggest unsolved families are:\n- round_robin_arbiter_unreal1 (28, signals 6-8) - small signals but hard for ltlsynt\n- full_arbiter_unreal1 (27, signals 4-12) - same situation\n- Various amba, g-unreal, chomp families\n\nLet me run two parallel campaigns:\n1. Continue tractable families with longer timeouts (those instances that weren't solved yet)\n2. Try spot game approach for round_robin_arbiter_unreal1 and full_arbiter_unreal1 which have small signals\n\n\nThe spot game approach could work for the arbiter families given their small signal counts, but the X-nesting depth is causing expensive game construction. I should test a few instances to see if this is actually feasible.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1737,"cache_read_input_tokens":95535,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1737},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6882dd44-b12a-40ea-abce-8556d98170ba","uuid":"26e2475b-7830-4efb-9047-31250b5c6c35"}
