This identified 25+ tractable families in one pass."," "," ## Benchmark landscape"," "," - 1586 instances from SYNTCOMP 2025 LTL selection"," - ~238 known realizable, ~111 known unrealizable, ~1237 unknown status","-- ~259 instances have reference solution sizes (ref_size)","-- Families include: amba, load_balancer, arbiter, collector, lift, ltl2dba, ltl2dpa, detector, etc.","+- Families include: amba, load_balancer, arbiter, collector, lift, ltl2dba, ltl2dpa, Spectra smart-home, etc."," "," ## Instance family insights"," ","-(To be filled as experiments reveal patterns)","+### Instantly solvable (ltlsynt --decompose, <1s)","+- **simple_arbiter_unreal1**: all 53 instances solved instantly. Decomposition is key.","+- **prioritized_arbiter_unreal1/2**: most solved instantly with decompose","+- **simple_arbiter_unreal2**: solved with decompose","+- **gf-unreal family**: individual instances, each solved in <1s","+- **F-G-contradiction**: solved with decompose","+- **g-unreal**: most solved with decompose in <1s"," ","-## Approach selection guide","+### Solvable with moderate effort (1-30s)","+- **ltl2dba_C2/E/Q/U1/theta**: realizable instances up to ~15 signals","+- **lift, lift_gr1, lift_unary_enc**: realizable, moderate circuits","+- **Spectra smart-home** (Lights, Coffee, Alarm, Shades, etc.): realizable, large circuits from spot but small from ltlsynt","+- **amba_decomposed_arbiter/encode**: solvable with decompose","+- **collector_v1/v3**: realizable, large game states"," ","-(To be filled based on experimental results. Key factors: n_inputs, n_outputs, spec structure, family)","+### Hard (>60s or intractable)","+- **full_arbiter_unreal1**: X-nesting depth (u parameter) causes exponential game construction time. u≤18 works (~22s), u>20 intractable","+- **round_robin_arbiter_unreal1**: similar to full_arbiter_unreal1, 3i/3o but deep nesting","+- **numeric**: huge formulas (29K+ chars), no ltlsynt algorithm works in 30s","+- **finding_nemo**: LTLf benchmarks using \"strong next\" operator, syfco can't parse","+- **amba_decomposed_lock**: large signal counts (12-402), intractable","+- **mux**: large signal counts (12-209)","+- **shift**: up to 1000 signals, infeasible"," ","-## Technique discoveries","+## Approach selection guide"," ","-(To be filled as new techniques are discovered and validated)","+| Signals | Family type | Best approach |","+|---------|-------------|---------------|","+| ≤8 | Any unreal | ltlsynt --decompose (try sd, ds, lar) |","+| ≤15 | Most families | ltlsynt --decompose + multiple algos |","+| ≤15 | Arbiter unreal (high params) | spot game (slow but works if game builds in time) |","+| 15-25 | Spectra/smart-home | ltlsynt-sd+decompose (produces smallest circuits) |","+| 15-25 | AMBA decomposed | ltlsynt+decompose |","+| >25 | Any | Likely intractable with current tools |"," ","+**For circuit quality**: Always re-optimize spot_game solutions with ltlsynt --algo=sd --decompose=yes --aiger=both+ud+dc","+"," ## Approaches that DON'T work"," ","-(To be filled with failed approaches and why they failed)","+- **Spot game on high-parameter arbiters**: X^u nesting with u>20 causes game construction to exceed any reasonable timeout (exponential in u)","+- **Bounded synthesis (current implementation)**: SAT encoding is incomplete, doesn't properly encode automaton transitions","+- **ltlsynt without --decompose**: Dramatically slower on multi-output specs","+- **Single algorithm**: No single ltlsynt algorithm dominates — sd, ds, lar each win on different instances","+- **Python subprocess nesting**: Running python3.14 via subprocess from python3.14 is unreliable for background tasks (output buffering issues)","+- **syfco on LTLf specs**: \"strong next\" operator not supported"," "," ## Current status"," ","-(To be updated with solve counts, quality metrics, and next priorities)","+**845 solved / 1586 total** (380 realizable, 465 unrealizable) = 53.3%","+","+**Next priorities**:","+1. Implement proper bounded synthesis (SAT-based) for small instances where both ltlsynt and spot time out","+2. Build custom approach for parametric arbiter_unreal families (exploit formula structure rather than building full game)","+3. Handle LTLf instances (finding_nemo family) — need direct LTLf synthesis","+4. Try `ltl2tgba` formula simplification before synthesis for borderline instances","+5. Explore ABC/yosys for post-synthesis circuit optimization (not currently installed)"]}],"originalFile":"# LTL Reactive Synthesis Expert Knowledge\n\n## Problem overview\n\n**Reactive synthesis**: given an LTL specification over input and output signals, construct a controller (Mealy/Moore machine) that satisfies the spec for ALL possible input sequences, or determine that no such controller exists (unrealizable).\n\n**Dual optimization goal**:\n1. Determine realizability status for as many instances as possible (both realizable and unrealizable count)\n2. For realizable instances, minimize AND gate count in the AIGER circuit encoding\n\n## Available primitives\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Analog in MaxSAT |\n|------|---------|-------------------|\n| `syfco` | Parse TLSF files → LTL formula, inputs, outputs | wcnf_parser |\n| `ltl2tgba` / `autfilt` | LTL → automaton conversion, automaton manipulation | SAT solver call |\n| PySAT + CaDiCaL | SAT encoding for bounded synthesis | Core-guided MaxSAT |\n| `ltlsynt` | Complete synthesis tool (baseline to beat) | RC2 |\n| Custom Python | Game solving, strategy extraction, circuit optimization | Local search |\n\n## Key algorithmic approaches\n\n### 1. Automaton-based pipeline (standard approach)\n1. Parse TLSF → LTL formula + I/O signals\n2. Convert LTL to universal co-Büchi automaton (UCW) or deterministic parity automaton (DPA)\n3. Build 2-player parity game from automaton\n4. Solve game (Zielonka's algorithm)\n5. Extract winning strategy → Mealy machine → AIGER circuit\n\n### 2. Bounded synthesis (SAT-based)\n- Encode \"exists k-state controller satisfying spec?\" as SAT\n- Try k = 1, 2, 4, 8, ... until SAT or timeout\n- Directly finds minimal-state controllers\n- Best for small specs where automaton blows up\n\n### 3. GR(1) fragment\n- Specs of form (∧ GF(a_i)) → (∧ GF(b_j)) with safety/justice conditions\n- Polynomial-time synthesis (no automaton construction needed)\n- Many SYNTCOMP instances are GR(1) — identify and exploit this\n\n### 4. Safety reduction\n- Some liveness specs can be reduced to safety via bounded lookahead\n- Safety games are simpler (reachability/safety, no parity conditions)\n\n### 5. Circuit minimization\n- After finding a correct controller, minimize the AIGER encoding\n- State minimization (merge equivalent states)\n- Logic minimization (reduce AND gates via BDD or ABC)\n- Re-encoding with fewer latches\n\n## Benchmark landscape\n\n- 1586 instances from SYNTCOMP 2025 LTL selection\n- ~238 known realizable, ~111 known unrealizable, ~1237 unknown status\n- ~259 instances have reference solution sizes (ref_size)\n- Families include: amba, load_balancer, arbiter, collector, lift, ltl2dba, ltl2dpa, detector, etc.\n\n## Instance family insights\n\n(To be filled as experiments reveal patterns)\n\n## Approach selection guide\n\n(To be filled based on experimental results. Key factors: n_inputs, n_outputs, spec structure, family)\n\n## Technique discoveries\n\n(To be filled as new techniques are discovered and validated)\n\n## Approaches that DON'T work\n\n(To be filled with failed approaches and why they failed)\n\n## Current status\n\n(To be updated with solve counts, quality metrics, and next priorities)\n"}}
